dcterms:description: FaceForensics++ is a dataset used for detecting manipulated facial images, containing 5,000 videos, with 1,000 real and 4,000 fake videos employing various manipulation methods.
dcterms:title: FaceForensics++ (FF++)

dcterms:description: The DD-VQA dataset includes triplets of images, questions, and answers related to the authenticity of images, designed to assess deepfake detection through common-sense reasoning.
dcterms:title: DD-VQA dataset
